      "heading": null,
      "description": "Thinly slice the peppers, onion and garlic."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat the coconut oil in a lidded pan and, when hot, add the peppers and onion. Sauté until the vegetables are soft. Add the garlic and cook for 2 mins. Stir through the rice, turmeric and herbs. Season with salt, add the stock and bring to the boil."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Place the lid on, reduce the heat to medium and cook for a further 10 mins before turning down to the lowest setting for a further 5 mins. Turn off the heat, remove the lid to let out some of the steam and place the lid back on. Leave to sit for 5 mins before fluffing the rice with a fork."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Serve with our Caribbean prawn curry."
